      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A LITTLE SILENCE NZ (8) has yet to miss a place in nine tries here. Produced another strong performance last start when he drew wide but battled on bravely for third. Switches to a standing start and comes off a 20m handicap but can win if he gets it right. LUVBITE (10) will have to overcome a 40m handicap but is flying at present with three successive wins here, scoring from the 30m mark two back. Could deliver again. STORMY VISTA NZ (3) has been good in two starts here since a spell. Drew on the back row and raced three wide without cover but stuck on to place fresh then started from a 20 handicap and raced parked when fourth last start. Race fit now so could strike from the front mark. ALTA TRIBUTE (9) has been tackling good company so will enjoy a class drop.",
